    J Hepatol
    TIPS prevents further decompensation and improves survival in patients with cirrhosis and portal hypertension in an individual patient data meta-analysis.
 The use of TIPS for refractory ascites and for prevention of variceal rebleeding reduces the incidence of a further decompensation event in comparison to SOC and increases survival in highly selected patients. Impact and implication A further decompensation (new or worsening ascites, variceal bleeding or rebleeding, hepatic encephalopathy, jaundice, HRS-AKI and SBP) in patients with cirrhosis is associated with a poor prognosis. Besides the already known role of TIPS in portal hypertension related complications, this study shows that TIPS is also able to decrease the overall risk of a further decompensation compared to standard of care and increases survival. These results strengthen the role of TIPS in the management of patients with cirrhosis and portal hypertension related complications.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 



