However, recent innovations in the characterization, and prognostication, of patients with PSC, in addition to new tools for medical management and emerging pharmacologic agents, give rise to the potential for meaningful progress in the next several years. This review summarizes current concepts in PSC and highlights areas of particular areas in need of further study.
