    The role of ETV4 in HCC: How transcription factors can inform immunotherapy combination treatments.
In conclusion, Xie et al 11 provides a framework for comprehensive profiling of TF dependencies in HCC by studying the role of ETV4 in promoting metastasis. By focusing on new combination therapy strategies targeting both upstream and downstream signaling pathways of aberrant TFs, especially pathways that create an immunosuppressive TME, they demonstrate an avenue for future studies in our tireless attempt to inhibit HCC progression and metastasis.
